eries</strong></h3><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Major hepatic resections for cancers like HCC, cholangiocarcinoma, liver metastasis and benign and infective diseases</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Radical cholecystectomy for Gall bladder cancer</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Whipple’s procedure</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgery to treat chronic pancreatitis&nbsp;e.g.- Frey procedure, LPJ etc</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pancreatic resections for pancreatic cancer&nbsp;e.g.- Laparoscopic distal pancreatectomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Choledochal cyst excision&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgeries for &nbsp;Bile duct injury and Biliary strictures&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic cholecystectomy, laparoscopic CBD exploration</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic splenectomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic cystogastrostomy, Cystojejunostomy for Pseudocyst</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgeries for Portal hypertension e.g.- Proximal splenorenal shunt and devascularisation procedure for EHPVO &amp; NCPF</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Laparoscopic cholecystectomy</strong></p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Small bowel and Colo-rectal Surgeries</strong></h3><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Small bowel resection</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgery for mesenteric cyst and mass</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgery for Crohn’s disease and abdominal tuberculosis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic appendectomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgery for ulcerative colitis- One stage/two-stage/three-stage surgery- Laparoscopic/open Total Proctocolectomy with Ileal pouch-anal anastomosis (IPAA)&nbsp;</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic and open surgery for colorectal cancer e.g.-&nbsp;Lap LAR, Lap APR, Lap hemicolectomy, Lap Sigmoidectomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Cytoreductive surgery and Hyperthermic intraperitoneal chemotherapy (HIPEC) for peritoneal carcinomatosis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Management and Surgery for Diverticulitis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic surgeries for rectal prolapse</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Perineal procedures for rectal prolapse</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">STARR procedure for ODS and rectal prolapse</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgery for rectovaginal fistula</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Laparoscopic Colorectal Surgery</strong></p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Other Surgical Procedures</strong></h3><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Large complex ventral hernias and recurrent hernia surgeries eg- Laparoscopic IPOM, Component separation with hernioplasty</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic surgery (TEP and TAPP) for inguinal hernia</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Minimal Invasive procedure for Haemorrhoids(MIPH)- for piles</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Surgery for fistula in ano and fissure in ano</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Emergency surgery for abdominal trauma and polytrauma, gastrointestinal bleeding,&nbsp; peritonitis, appendicitis, intestinal obstructions etc</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Patients with critical illness such as acute pancreatitis, enterocutaneous fistula, gastrointestinal bleeding, perforation peritonitis and those undergoing supra-major operations are managed by a modern Surgical Intensive Care Unit managed by well-trained intensivist</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"https://choithramhospital.com/admin/uploads/editor/699258637.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"border-width: initial; border-style: none; height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 0px; box-shadow: none;\"><strong>Laparoscopic hernia Surgery- Mesh repair(TEP)</strong></p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Metabolic Surgery/ Bariatric Surgery</strong></h3><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Laparoscopic Sleeve Gastrectomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Roux-En-Y&nbsp; gastric bypass</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Mini gastric bypass</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"https://choithramhospital.com/admin/uploads/editor/629632379.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"border-width: initial; border-style: none; height: auto; max-width: 100%; border-radius: 0px; box-shadow: none;\"><strong>Bariatric Surgery- Laparoscopic Sleeve Gastrectomy</strong></p>', 0),
(12, 'General Surgery', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 44px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); clear: both;\">Best General Surgery Hospital in Indore</h1><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Overview</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of General Surgery provides surgical interventions that focus on the endocrine system, gastrointestinal tract, liver, colon, and other major parts of the human body. Some of the common procedures include appendix, gallbladder removals, colonoscopies, thyroidectomies, hernia and bariatric surgeries.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The department of General Surgery at Choithram Hospital&nbsp; provides its patients with the services employing cutting-edge surgical care. The department also specializes in Laparoscopic and robotic surgeries (also known as key-hole surgery or minimally invasive surgery), which helps in providing patients with a variety of treatments in the fields of gynecology, gastroenterology and urology. Using such advanced techniques helps in the speedy recovery of the patients with minimal amount of tissue damage, minimal blood loss, reduced risk of developing infection and hence, minimal pain and discomfort. The general surgery team has its expertise in providing complete patient safety and satisfaction by using all the latest diagnosing and surgical techniques.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><b>Best General Surgery Hospital in Indore – Choithram Hospital</b></p>', 0),
(13, 'Gastroenterology', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 44px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); clear: both;\">Gastroenterology Hospital in Indore</h1><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Overview</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Department of Gastroenterology at Choithram Hospital and Research Centre is one of the most advanced centers to treat diseases of entire Gastro-Intestinal Tract; Liver, Pancreas, Gallbladder. It is equipped with most advanced state of the art endoscopes to diagnose and treat the diseases. The Department of Gastroenterology is also recognized for liver transplantation. The department is well supported by Surgical Gastroenterology for all complicated GI surgeries like Whipple’s; Surgeries of GI tract; Liver and Pancreas. Most advanced Interventional Radiological Procedures like TACE, TIPS, RFA for liver cancer are routine procedures in the department.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><b>Services</b></span></h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Diagnostic UGI Endoscopy</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology uses the Olympus Exera 190 scopes including NBI for early detection of cancer and other GI diseases and disorders.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Therapeutic UGI Endoscopy</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology carries out the following procedures:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Endoscopic Variceal Ligation<br>Hemoclipping</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Foreign body removal</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">EMR/ESD for early cancer</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Poem for Achalasia</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Endoscopic Dilatation</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Prosthesis Placement</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Glue Injection</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Diagnostic Colonoscopy</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology carries out diagnostic colonoscopy to identify the disease or problem for further consultation.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Therapeutic Colonoscopy</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology carries out the following procedures:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Polypectomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Hemoclipping</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">EMR, ESD</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Prosthesis Replacement</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Endoscopic Retrograde Cholangio-Pancreatography (ERCP)</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology carries out all kinds of therapeutic ERCPs with stone removal from CBD, MPD, Stent Replacement, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Endoscopic Ultrasound (EUS)</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology carries out all diagnostic EUS for:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Hepatobiliary</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Mediastinal Lesions ESP</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Fine Needle Aspiration Cytology (FNAC)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Fine needle aspiration biopsy (FNAB)</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology carries out all therapeutic EUS:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Cystogastrostomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Choledocho-Duodenostomy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Hepatico- Gastrostomy</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Argon Plasma Coagulation (APC)</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Argon plasma coagulation is a medical endoscopic procedure for controlling bleeding, telangiectasia and radiation proctitis.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Capsule Endoscopy</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology offers capsule endoscopy for:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Wireless endoscopy ESP</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Diagnosis of Small Bowel Diseases like Crown’s disease; tuberculosis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Disease of Large Bowel</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><b>Single Ballon Enteroscopy</b></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology performs single balloon enteroscopy for diagnosis and endoscopic treatment of small bowel diseases</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Manometry</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Gastroenterology performs the following medical procedures:<br>Oesophageal Manometry to diagnose ailments in patients having chest pain with no coronary artery disease. It’s is also used for diagnosis of Achalasia and Gerd; to diffuse oesophageal spasm.<br>Anorectal Manometry for diagnosis of chronic constipation, stool incontinence and defecation disorder.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><b>Liver Clinic</b></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Liver Clinic caters to all patients presenting with jaundice, itching, swelling over feet, abdominal distension, blood vomiting, blood in stool and black stools. These symptoms represent variety of acute and chronic liver diseases, and liver failure due to: viruses, excessive consumption of alcohol, overuse of certain medical drugs, metabolic disorder like Wilson’s disease; and autoimmune liver diseases. The Liver Clinic caters to the requirement of specialised tests for diagnosis and long term treatment.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Liver Transplant Clinic</strong></h3><div style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Liver Transplant Clinic is a specialised clinic for evaluating patients who need liver transplant and; for patients who ave undergone liver transplant and require.</span></span></p><h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>IBD Clinic</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\">The IBD Clinic is for patients suffering from ulcerative colitis, Crohn’s disease, indeterminate colitis, microscopic colitis and intestinal tuberculosis. These patients not only require long term treatment, however, they need to be screened at appropriate time to diagnose the arising complications and sequelae for their cure.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Pancreas Clinic</strong></h3><div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Pancreas Clinic is for patients suffering from recurrent attacks of pancreatitis, chronic pancreatitis, pancreatitis due to excessive alcohol consumption, children and adolescent who may have hereditary pancreatitis or idiopathic pancreatitis. The Pancreas Clinic gives special attention to the diet and development of the patients.</div><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\">&nbsp;</h3><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Paediatric GI and Liver Clinic</strong></h3></div><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Paediatric GI and Liver Clinic treats children suffering from recurrent abdominal pain, liver diseases due to metabolic disorder, chronic diarrhoea and not gaining height or weight.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><b>Best&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-ff6f72c ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif;\">Gastroenterology Hospital In Indore – Choithram Hospital</span></b></p>', 0);
