(21, 'Pediatric Surgery', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 44px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); clear: both;\">Pediatric Surgery Hospital in Indore</h1><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Overview<br></strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Pediatrics in Choithram Hospital is one of the earliest to pioneer many advancements in pediatric care in central India including pediatric ventilation, neonatal intensive care and pediatric subspecialities for the last 40 years.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Pediatric Intensive Care Unit<br></strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Pediatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU) at Choithram Hospital is a multidisciplinary unit that provides care for infants, children and adolescents who become critically ill or injured. It has 8 beds and a full time Pediatric Intensivist and trained nurses and residents round the clock.<br>It is a comprehensive set up well equipped to handle pediatric ventilation, pediatric peritoneal dialysis, hemodialysis and total parenteral nutrition.<br>The many physicians, nurses and allied medical care professionals who work in the PICU have the knowledge, skill and judgment to quickly assess and treat your child so he can achieve the best outcomes possible from critical illness or injury.<br>Equipped with advanced technology, our multidisciplinary team improves survival, speeds recovery, minimizes disability and relieves pain and suffering in a caring and respectful manner.<br>Conditions that commonly cause critical illness and injury include:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Severe infection</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Poisoning</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Drug overdose</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Trauma</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Neurological, cardiac or renal problems</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Congenital anomalies and pediatric surgery</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Hematological or immunological disorders</li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"color: rgb(227, 8, 8);\">The Neonatal Intensive care Unit ( NICU)</span><br></strong></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">This 20 bedded level III NICU is accredited by the National Neonatology Forum. It has a full time in-house neonatologist, trained nurses and residents. There is also a fellowship program in neonatal care. Our unit is equipped with the latest technology and advances in neonatal medicine. For more than 25 years, we’ve cared for babies with all types of conditions and congenital malformations.<br>We provide care for neonates who need acute medical care, including ventilation, dialysis, total parenteral nutrition, therapeutic hypothermia, phototherapy, multidisciplinary evaluations, complex surgical intervention. Our success stories include preterm neonates as small as 600 grams and prolonged ventilation as long as 1-2 months.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Our patient services</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We have 6 days a week ( Monday to Saturday) out patient clinics catering to general pediatrics with daily vaccination services.<br>We have several sub speciality services including Pediatric Neurology, Pediatric Cardiology, Pediatric Gastroenterology.<br>Pediatric Neurology- Patients with developmental delay, epilepsy, autism, inborn errors of metabolism, duchene muscular dystrophy, malformations of the brain are evaluated and managed using state of the art radiological, metabolic and genetic tests. Ketogenic diet for difficult to treat epilepsy is also available here.<br>Pediatric cardiology- Patients with congenital heart disorders such as tetralogy of fallot, TGA, TAPVC, VSD, ASD, PDA,AS,PS, coarctation of aorta, arrhythmias etc are evaluated by our specialist pediatric cardiologist. Pediatric ECHO, catheterisation, and interventions are carried out here. Many cases of device closure of ASD, VSD or PDA, balloon dilatation of coarctation of aorta, aortic or pulmonary stenosis, PDA stenting, balloon dilatation and management of takayasu arteritis , pericardial effusion drainage have been done efficiently at our centre with good results and safety.<br>Fetal Echo (specialised echo done before birth in pregnancy) is available here which can detect congenital heart defect and rhythm abnormalities before birth so their counselling and management can be planned/ done in utero or early after birth.<br>Pediatric Gastroenterology:Choithram hospital is a pioneer in providing dedicated Pediatric Gastroenterology services in Madhya Pradesh through the services of a well qualified and trained Pediatric Gastroenterologist. Patients with celiac disease, chronic diarrhea, chronic constipation, recurrent abdominal pain, liver disease, upper and lower GI bleeding are managed here under specialist care. Department also has the state of art endoscopy facilities including diagnostic and therapeutic upper GI endoscopy, colonoscopy, Pediatric ERCP and EUS, Anorectal and esophageal manometry, 24h pH monitoring.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We have 6 days a week ( Monday to Saturday) out patient clinics catering to general pediatrics with daily vaccination services.<br>We have several sub speciality services including Pediatric Neurology, Pediatric Cardiology, Pediatric Gastroenterology.<br>Pediatric Neurology- Patients with developmental delay, epilepsy, autism, inborn errors of metabolism, duchene muscular dystrophy, malformations of the brain are evaluated and managed using state of the art radiological, metabolic and genetic tests. Ketogenic diet for difficult to treat epilepsy is also available here.<br>Pediatric cardiology- Patients with congenital heart disorders such as tetralogy of fallot, TGA, TAPVC, VSD, ASD, PDA,AS,PS, coarctation of aorta, arrhythmias etc are evaluated by our specialist pediatric cardiologist. Pediatric ECHO, catheterisation, and interventions are carried out here. Many cases of device closure of ASD, VSD or PDA, balloon dilatation of coarctation of aorta, aortic or pulmonary stenosis, PDA stenting, balloon dilatation and management of takayasu arteritis , pericardial effusion drainage have been done efficiently at our centre with good results and safety.<br>Fetal Echo (specialised echo done before birth in pregnancy) is available here which can detect congenital heart defect and rhythm abnormalities before birth so their counselling and management can be planned/ done in utero or early after birth.<br>Pediatric Gastroenterology:Choithram hospital is a pioneer in providing dedicated Pediatric Gastroenterology services in Madhya Pradesh through the services of a well qualified and trained Pediatric Gastroenterologist. Patients with celiac disease, chronic diarrhea, chronic constipation, recurrent abdominal pain, liver disease, upper and lower GI bleeding are managed here under specialist care. Department also has the state of art endoscopy facilities including diagnostic and therapeutic upper GI endoscopy, colonoscopy, Pediatric ERCP and EUS, Anorectal and esophageal manometry, 24h pH monitoring.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Thalassemia Day Care Centre</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We cater to about 100 patients with Thalassemia and Sickle Cell Anaemia and provide packed red blood transfusions, chelation services and supportive medical services to them at subsidised cost.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Vaccination Centre<br></strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">All pediatric vaccines are available Monday to Friday 9 Am to 4 PM in the Pediatric OPD by trained doctors and nurses according to the guidelines of the Indian Academy of pediatrics.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Prayas<br></strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We have a comprehensive centre for special children including children with autism, cerebral palsy, mental retardation and other disabilities. Our staff include occupational therapists, physiotherapists, special educators, speech therapists and clinical psychologists.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Pediatric Transport Services</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We have a 24×7 ambulance service with trained nurses and doctor support to transport sick newborns and children from nearby hospitals. The contact number is 9109158206.</p>', 0),
(22, 'Psychiatry', '<h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Overview</span></strong></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Psychiatry treats with all kinds of behavioral and emotional problems which include child psychiatry, adolescent psychiatry, geriatric psychiatry, substance dependency, mood disorders such as dysthymia and depression, and anxiety spectrum disorders. The consultants take a detailed psychiatric history, mental status examination and perform a psychological evaluation of patients. Pharma-therapy and counseling services are provided to patients and attendants by therapists and counselors. With the help of the faculty of Choithram College of Nursing, we have started a Multi-Disciplinary Behaviour Intervention Unit for the benefit of patients. The Department of Psychiatry provides the following services:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">De-addiction Programme</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Stress Management</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Cognitive Behavioural Therapy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Psychodynamic Therapy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Neuropsychiatry – evaluation and treatment for patients with organic brain lesions</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Outpatient Behavioural Services</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Inpatient Psychiatric Treatment</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pharmacotherapy (individual &amp; group therapy)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Milieu Treatment</li></ul><div style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><i><b>Psychiatrist Doctor in Indore</b></i></div>', 0),
(23, 'Physiotherapy', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 44px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); clear: both;\">Physiotherapy Centre in Indore</h1><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Overview</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">High Standard physiotherapy treatment is provided with modern physiotherapy equipment by well-qualified faculty with different specialization fields like musculoskeletal and sports injuries, neurology, cardiothoracic, obstetrics and gynaecology, and pediatrics. Services are provided on both OPD and IPD basis from 8:30 AM to 6:30 PM.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Services</strong></span></h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Sports Injury Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We offer fitness and pelvic strength training advice and treatment to antenatal and postnatal mothers. We provide advice and counseling on the importance of breastfeeding as well.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Athletes and sportspersons who suffer from any type of injury are treated and rehabilitated in our department. We provide injury prevention coaching and muscle conditioning protocol. We render plyometric and eccentric training.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Musculoskeletal Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We treat orthopaedic conditions like OA, RA, LBA, disc prolapse, fractures, dislocations, inflammatory, degenerative, traumatic, soft tissue injuries. We run special clinics for knee and back.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Neurological Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We treat nerve injuries, LMN, UMN lesions, Spinal Cord injuries, Head injuries, stroke and paralytic patients. Patients stay at Dharmshala of hospital and avail services for a long time when required. Both adult and pediatric patients are treated here.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Cardio-Pulmonary Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We offer pre and post-operative treatment and rehabilitation to all cardiac and lung conditions like myocardial infarction, ASD, VSD, asthma, bronchiectasis, emphysema, Etc. We have a treadmill training facility in Cardiac Rehabilitation</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Paediatric Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Along with the pediatric department and prayas we provide physiotherapy services for disabled or specially-abled children like children with polio, muscular dystrophy, cerebral palsy, autism, delayed milestones, congenital postoperative deformity patients.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Obstetrics and Gynae Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We offer fitness and pelvic strength training advice and treatment to antenatal and postnatal mothers. We provide advice and counseling on the importance of breastfeeding as well.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Geriatric Rehabilitation</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We provide balance training and co-ordination training advice and treatment alongside fitness program to old age patients to deal with their imbalance problems and associated falls</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\">Burns Rehabilitation</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We have a dedicated physiotherapist to deal with burns patients with a team effort of departments of surgery, plastic surgery, and occupational therapy.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>ICU Services</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We provide high standard physiotherapy management in all ICUs with chest manipulations, spirometer, suctioning and pressure sore prevention and treatment.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Fitness</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We provide fitness and agility protocols to all patients who suffer from overweight or obesity. We provide fitness exercises to sportspersons, geriatrics and young mothers.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Pain Relief</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">We work on pain relief with modern equipment like laser, ultrasound therapy, micro-wave diathermy, sound wave diathermy, wax bath, contrast bath, phonophoresis, Iontophoresis, IFT and also with manual therapy like mobilization and manipulation.</p>', 0),
(24, 'Radiology', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 44px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); clear: both;\">Best Radiology Hospital in Indore</h1><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Overview</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Department of Radiology and imaging services at CHRC is a full service, academic imaging department that performs over one lakh screening, diagnostic and interventional procedures annually. The goal of the department is to provide every patient with timely access to the most sophisticated medical imaging technology in a compassionate setting and to quickly deliver accurate medical reports to referring physicians and surgeons. The Department is equipped with state of the art world-class x-ray machines, ultra-sonography machines with dedicated probes for ARFI, small joint sonography and intraoperative sonography, DEXA scan, RFA machine, 128 slice CT scan, 1.5 T MRI and PET CT scanner which are integrated with PACS to view anywhere and at any time.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Services</strong></span></h2><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Computerized Radiography</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Computerized radiology is the branch of radiology that uses ionizing radiation (x-rays) to visualize the bones and organs in order to provide medical information needed to diagnose a problem.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">X-ray of all the parts of the body</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Barium Studies (single and double-contrast)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Barium Swallow</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Barium Meal</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Barium Meal Follow Through 3)Barium Enema</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Gastrographin Studies</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Loopogram</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Urographic Studies</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Intravenous Pyelography (IVP)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Ascending Urethrography (AGU)/Retrograde Urethrography (RGU)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Micturating Cystourethrogram (MCU)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">NephrostogramHysterosalpingography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">T Tube Cholangiography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Fistulogram</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Sinogram</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Ultrasonography</strong></span></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Ultrasonography is a diagnostic medical procedure that uses sound waves to produce images on a screen, which allows medical providers to view internal structures of the body. It is not harmful to the body and fetus.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Routine Ultrasonography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Abdomen</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Renal</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pelvis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Obstetric</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Ultrasonography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Early Pregnancy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Early Anomaly Scan</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Target Scan</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Biophysical Profile</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Transvaginal Sonography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Fetal Echo Scan</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Musculoskeletal Sonography of Muscles and Joints</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Small Joint’s Sonography by Special high-frequency hockey stick probe</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Breast Sonography with elastography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Acoustic Radiation Force Impulse (ARFI) for liver and spleen</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Thyroid Sonography<br>Trans-rectal Prostate Sonography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Neo-Natal Sonogram</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Doppler Studies</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Carotid Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Arteriovenous (Fistula) Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Obstetric Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Porto venous Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Renal Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Limb Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Transplant Graft Doppler – Renal and Liver</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Mesenteric Doppler</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">US-guided RFA, FNAC, Biopsy, Drainage procedure</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Computed Tomography Scan (CT)</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Computed Tomography Scan uses ionizing radiation (x-rays) and computer processing to produce three-dimensional imaging of the body. The patient may need contrast dye to improve the computed image. The patient may need to avoid eating or drinking for 4 to 6 hours before the test. We use 128 slices Siemens machine with the fastest wide gantry.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT Scan</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Brain</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">PNS</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Neck</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Chest</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Routine</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">HRCT</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Abdomen</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pelvis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT Angiography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Cerebral</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Neck</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pulmonary</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Abdominal</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Limbs</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT Coronary</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Angiography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT Enterography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT Dental Scan – to know 3 Dimensional details of individual tooth</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT Coronary Calcium Scoring</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">CT guided RFA, FNAC, Biopsy, Drainage procedures</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Virtual Bronchoscopy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Virtual Colonoscopy</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\">Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI)</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Magnetic Resonance Imaging uses a magnetic field, radio-frequency impulse and a computer to produce detailed images of body structures in multiple dimensions. We have a 3 T, wide-bore MRI machine with silent scan features (no noise gantry).</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Sleep Apnoea Study</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Defecography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Cochlear Implant Study</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Perianal and Rectovaginal Fistula Study</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">MRI Studies of Brain</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Neck</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Abdomen</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Limbs</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pelvis</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Speciality Services</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Breast Imaging</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Prostate Imaging</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Liver and Cardiac</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Iron Quantification</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Liver Fat Quantification<br>Fetal MRI</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">MR enterography<br>Spectroscopy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Pediatric imaging with or without sedation</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Magnetic Resonance Cholangiopancreatography (MRCP)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Contrast-Enhanced MRI</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Musculoskeletal MRI</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Triple Phase and Multi-Phase MRI for liver</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">MR Contrast Angiography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">MR Non- Contrast Angiography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">MR Venogram</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Dual-Energy X-Ray Absorptiometry (DEXA) Scan</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry scan is a special type of x-ray that measures bone mineral density, whole-body muscle mass to give an outlook of bone strength.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Whole Body DEXA Scan</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Regional DEXA Scan</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Interventional Radiology</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Radio-Frequency Ablation of varicose veinsInterventional radiology is a new sub-specialty of radiology providing minimally invasive image-guided treatment of many diseases.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Fine-needle aspiration biopsy (FNAC)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Biopsy</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Drainage</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Inferior Vena Cava Filter</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Biliary Drainage</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Percutaneous biliary drainage(PTBD)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">PTBD with Internalisation</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Trans-jugular Intra-hepatic Portosystemic Shunt (TIPS)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Direct intra-hepatic portocaval shunt (DIPS)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Trans-jugular Liver Biopsy (TJLB)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Chemo Embolisation of Tumor (TACE)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Radio-Frequency Ablation of Tumor (RFA)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Venous Thrombolysis for DVT</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Uterine Artery Embolisation</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Bronchial Artery EmbolisationRena</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Artery</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">StentingCerebral Angiography</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Peripheral angiography and angioplasty</li></ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Molecular Imaging and Nuclear Medicine</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The term molecular imaging can be broadly defined as the in vivo characterization and measurement of biologic processes at the cellular and molecular level.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Positron Emission Tomography (PET)</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Computed Tomography (CT) Scan</li><li style=\"line-height: 26px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 10px !important;\">Gamma Camera</li></ul><div style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><b>Best Radiology Hospital in Indore – Choithram Hospital&nbsp;</b></div>', 0),
(25, 'Rheumatology', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 44px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); clear: both;\">Rheumatology Hospital in Indore</h1><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Overview</strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The Department of Rheumatology treats rheumatic diseases such as arthritis. Left untreated, rheumatic diseases cause pain, limit the range of motion and lead to joint deformities, which in turn can cause loss of muscle strength. Choithram Hospital and Research Centre’s Rheumatology Department helps patients avoid the vicious circle by extending expert services to help regain a healthier, more active lifestyle.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>Brief Outline of the Department’s functions/ services/ diseases/ treatment:</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Experienced Rheumatologist. Best treatment services provided to patients suffering from various rheumatic diseases like Rheumatoid Arthritis (RA), Ankylosing Spondylosis (AS), SLE (Systemic Lupus Erythematosis), Gout, Scleroderma, Vasculitis, Sjogren’s Syndrome, Myositis, Paediatric Rheumatologic Diseases. Provide DMARD Therapy, latest Biologic Therapy, Physiotherapy guidance.</p><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-size: 22px; clear: both;\"><strong>The Department of Rheumatology offers the following facilities &amp; services:</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Immunology Lab to conduct medical procedures and diagnostic tests like the rheumatoid factor, Anti-CCP antibody, ANA and various other antibodies testing.<br>Dedicated physiotherapy services<br>Synovial (joint) fluid analysis<br>Special auto-antibodies<br>Pediatric rheumatology is a specialty were rheumatologists are specifically trained to be highly skilled in managing various arthritis conditions and autoimmune diseases as Juvenile idiopathic arthritis(earlier called as juvenile rheumatoid arthritis), SLE, myositis, localized scleroderma, and various immunodeficiency disease.<br>Fully equipped diagnostic laboratory services with accurate testing of RA Factor, Anti-CCP Antibody, ANA, ENA Panel, HLA B27</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\"><strong>Services<br></strong></span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">DMARDs<br>Biological Therapy with complete screening and under the proper observation<br>Full OPD &amp; IPD Services<br>Diagnostic Services like CT Scan, MRI, Musculoskeletal USG<br>Laboratory facilities</p>', 0);
