(7, 'Dr. RAJENDRA K.AANJNE', 'MD (RADIATION ONCOLOGY)', 'CONSULTANT RADIATION ONCOLOGY', 'Radiation Oncology', 'Head & Neck cancer, Breast Cancer, Intracranial tumors (Brain Tumors), Gynecological cancer, Gastro Intestinal malignancy, Prostate cancer', 'MON TO SAT', '09:00 AM TO 05:00 PM', '<h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Dr. Rajendra Anjane</span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Consultant Radiation Oncology</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Professional Summar</span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Dr.Rajendra Kumar Anjane has completed his Bachelors of Medicine and Bachelors of Surgery (MBBS) from&nbsp;<strong>M.G.M. Medical College, Indore (M.P.)</strong>&nbsp;in year 2001 and MD in in Radiotherapy from&nbsp;<strong>S.G.P.T. Cancer Hospital</strong>&nbsp;in year 2008. In 2010, he completed his Certificate Course in Palliative care from Indian Association of Palliative Care India.</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Technical Skills</span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">He has expertise in the area of:</p><ol style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 20px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li>Head &amp; Neck cancer</li><li>Breast Cancer</li><li>Intracranial tumors (Brain Tumors)</li><li>Gynecological cancer</li><li>Gastro Intestinal malignancy</li><li>Prostate cancer</li></ol><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Scientific and medical Societies Memebership</span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">1. Association of Radiation oncologist of India – LM-1112</p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Work Experience</span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">i. Rotating Internship in M.G.M. Medical College, Indore (M.P.) in year 2001.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">ii. III<span style=\"position: relative; font-size: 12px; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;\">rd</span>&nbsp;ICRO/AROI Teaching Course on “Management of Carcinoma Cervix” at PGIMER, Chandigarh in year 2007.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">iii. Residency training in Radiotherapy from S.G.P.T. Cancer Hospital, M.G.M. Medical College, Indore (M.P.) from 2003 to 2008.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">iv. Senior Resident Delhi state cancer institute GTB Hospital, New Delhi from 2007-2008.</span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 19px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(209, 37, 34); font-size: 19px; clear: both;\"><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline;\">Alternate Courses</span></h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; font-family: Robot